column9: It seemed more straight to the point and I think I agreed with it more overall.
column10: because of the way it sorted options
column12: The red robot seems to think more logically and it makes it more predictable and more likely to make decisions that make sense. The blue robot appears to be less predictable and uses "feeling" when making decisions.
column13: This robust seemed more lively and natural, compared to the blue robot.
column14: The answers that it gave were more consistent with the way I would answer. the movements were a bit smoother with the blue robot than the red robot, especially in the earlier videos.
column15: The red robot seemed to use language better.  The red robot seemed more approachable because it seemed “friendlier”.
column16: Red Robot is smarter and more attentive
